<section xml:id="sec-intervals-c-natural-minor" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>C Natural Minor Scale</title>

  <p>In C natural minor, the interval pattern differs from the major scale in that the third, sixth, and seventh scale degrees are lowered.</p>
  <p>All natural minor scales follow the same interval pattern, so any natural minor scale can be built by using this pattern of major and minor seconds.</p>
  <p>The C natural minor scale notes are C, D, E<flat/>, F, G, A<flat/>, B<flat/>, and C.</p>

  <p>A natural minor scale is the relative minor of a major scale. The A minor natural scale uses these same notes, the sixth note of the major scale becoming the root note of the relative minor.
ie.) the notes of the A Minor Natural Scale are A, B, C, D, E, F, G and A.</p>
<p>C minor natural is the relative minor of E<flat/> major. <!--(See Circle of Fifths for all Scale relationships.  (<xref ref="circle-of-fifths" text="type-global" />)--></p>
  <figure xml:id="fig-c-natural-minor-scale-notation">
    <caption>C natural minor scale notation on a musical staff (ascending and descending).</caption>
    <image>
      <latex-image>
        <![CDATA[
\begin{music}
  \nobarnumbers
  \setclef10
  \startextract
  \notes \qa c \qa d \qa {_e} \qa f \qa g \qa {_h} \qa {_i} \qa j \qa {_i} \qa {_h} \qa g \qa f \qa {_e} \qa d \qa c \en
  \endextract
\end{music}
        ]]>
      </latex-image>
    </image>
  </figure>

  <figure xml:id="fig-intervals-c-natural-minor-ascending-table">
    <caption>Examples of intervals with notation and semitone counts (C natural minor scale ascending).</caption>
    <image>
      <latex-image>
        <![CDATA[
\newcommand{\MusiC}[1]{\adjustbox{trim=145pt 0pt 140pt 0pt, valign=c}{%
  \begin{music}
    \nobarnumbers
    \setclef10
    \startextract
    \notes #1
    \endextract
  \end{music}}}

\begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|c|c|c|}
  \hline
  Interval & Quality & Notes & On Staff & Number of Semitones & Count\\
  \hline
  Second & Major & C~-~D & \MusiC{\qa c \qa d \en} & 2 & 3\\
  \hline
  Second & Minor & D~-~E flat & \MusiC{\qa d \qa {_e} \en} & 1 & 2\\
  \hline
  Second & Major & E flat~-~F & \MusiC{\qa {_e} \qa f \en} & 2 & 3\\
  \hline
  Second & Major & F~-~G & \MusiC{\qa f \qa g \en} & 2 & 3\\
  \hline
  Second & Minor & G~-~A flat & \MusiC{\qa g \qa {_h} \en} & 1 & 2\\
  \hline
  Second & Major & A flat~-~B flat & \MusiC{\qa {_h} \qa {_i} \en} & 2 & 3\\
  \hline
  Second & Major & B flat~-~C & \MusiC{\qa {_i} \qa j \en} & 2 & 3\\
  \hline
\end{tabular}
        ]]>
      </latex-image>
    </image>
  </figure>

</section>
